## Database Access Rules

<!-- Specify which databases exist, how to connect, and any constraints.
     This is critical for scripts that run queries. -->

- **Read queries** should target: _e.g. replica pods with label `postgres-operator.crunchydata.com/role=replica`_
- **Connection method**: _e.g. `kubectl exec` into the pod, use `psql -U postgres -d <dbname>`_
- **Write operations**: _e.g. Never run write queries from monitoring tasks_
- **Available databases**: _e.g. `appdb`, `usearch`, `analytics`_

## Naming Conventions

<!-- Describe how resources are named so scripts can discover them reliably. -->

- **Pod labels**: _e.g. `app.kubernetes.io/name=<component>`_
- **Service names**: _e.g. `<component>-svc` in each namespace_
- **ConfigMaps / Secrets**: _e.g. `<component>-config`, `<component>-credentials`_

## Common Environment Variables

