     These map to workspace secrets or user-provided values. -->

| Variable | Description | Example | Secret? |
|----------|-------------|---------|---------|
| `CONTEXT` | Kubernetes context | `gke_my-project_us-central1_prod` | No |
| `NAMESPACE` | Target namespace | `backend-services` | No |
| `kubeconfig` | Path to kubeconfig file | _(injected by runner)_ | Yes |

## Task Authoring Rules

<!-- Specific rules that ALL scripts in this workspace must follow.
     These override general defaults. -->

- _e.g. Always use `--context=$CONTEXT` with kubectl commands_
- _e.g. Never use `kubectl delete` in read-only tasks_
- _e.g. Include resource limits in issue descriptions_
- _e.g. Timeouts: set `--request-timeout=30s` on all kubectl calls_

## SLX Conventions

<!-- How SLXs should be named, tagged, and organized in this workspace. -->

- **Naming**: _e.g. `<component>-<check-type>` → `postgres-replication-lag`_
- **Access tag**: _e.g. Most monitoring tasks use `read-only`_
- **Data tag**: _e.g. Database queries use `logs-bulk`, config checks use `config`_
- **SLI schedule**: _e.g. Health checks run every 5 minutes, heavy queries every hour_

## Known Gotchas

<!-- Pitfalls, edge cases, or non-obvious behaviors that script authors should know. -->

- _e.g. PGO replica pods restart during maintenance windows (Tue 2-4am UTC)_
- _e.g. The `analytics` namespace uses a different kubeconfig context_
- _e.g. Redis Sentinel requires connecting to the sentinel service first_
